==English==
===Etymology===
from ''Jean Baptiste Joseph Fourier'', its inventor
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''[[Fourier]] [[transform]]'''
#{{mathematics}} a process that expresses a [[function]] as a [[sum]] or [[integral]] of [[sinusoidal]] functions multiplied by [[coefficient]]s; it has many [[scientific]] and [[industrial]] [[applications]], especially in [[signal]] [[processing]]

